HEADWORD: Cestidae
<hw>Cestidae</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>A family of invertebrates
coextensive with the order <ord>Cestida</ord>; ctenophores having a
greatly flattened and elongated body.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> family <fam>Cestidae</fam>.</syn>⟦br⟧
